RM  18156323
RT  Determination of glycosyltransferase specificities for the Escherichia
RT  coli O111 O antigen by a generic approach.
RA  Stevenson G, Dieckelmann M, Reeves PR;
RL  Appl Environ Microbiol. 2008;74:1294-1298.
CC  The O111 O-antigen is observed in E. coli strain 11128. The structure
CC  of the O111 antigen is a branched pentasaccharide containing two
CC  colitose sugars [1]. The O111 biosynthetic cluster encodes three sugar
CC  transferases WbdHLM, the wzx and wzy components as well as the enzymes
CC  for the biosynthesis of GDP-L-colitose from D-fructose-6P via
CC  GDP-mannose.  One of the transferases, WbdM, is responsible for
CC  attaching both colitose residues at both the 3 and 6 positions of
CC  alpha-D-glucose as the last steps of the monomer synthesis.   
